National Security Advisor Sullivan met with representatives of The Elders, an organization of former world leaders founded by Nelson Mandela. They discussed the importance of U.S. leadership in addressing various global threats, such as climate change, nuclear arms control, the COVID-19 pandemic, health security, and conflicts in Ethiopia and other parts of the world. The representatives included Mary Robinson, Gro Harlem Brundtland, Ricardo Lagos, Juan Manuel Santos, Hina Jilani, and David Nussbaum.